metadata.name: Lady Macbeth
metadata.description:
"Lady Macbeth (or The Sense of Guilt Comes Home to Roost)"

Digital Painting / 6862x10070 pixels / 2022

The inspiration for this piece comes from Lady Macbeth, a leading character in William Shakespeare's tragedy "Macbeth", who urges her husband into committing regicide, after which she becomes queen of Scotland.
Macbeth turns into a murderous tyrant and she is driven to madness by guilt over their crimes. Ultimately she kills herself.
